Package: CEDMr
Title: Capability-Ecological Developmental Model (CEDM) Analysis Toolkit
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Subir", "Hait",
           email   = "hait@example.com",
           role    = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0004-9871-9677"))
Description: Implements the Capability-Ecological Developmental Model (CEDM)
    for studying how socioeconomic status (SES), health indicators (e.g., BMI),
    and ecological contexts jointly shape academic achievement. Provides tools
    for: (1) classifying ecological capability regimes (amplifying, neutral,
    compensatory); (2) fitting the CEDM capability-conversion production function
    with moderation and three-way interaction terms; (3) doubly robust causal
    mediation analysis; (4) random-effects within-between (REWB) decomposition;
    (5) nonlinear moderation via restricted cubic splines; (6) BMI/health
    trajectory clustering; and (7) sensitivity analysis using Frank's ITCV and
    robustness-to-replacement (RIR) indices. The package operationalizes all
    five CEDM theoretical propositions into directly callable R functions and
    is designed to work with any longitudinal multi-level dataset, including
    ECLS-K:2011 and similar surveys.
